"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## \\n\\n![Mundo Lingo Ambassador at work in Oslo ](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/2KDjVn9uTrSZKckCjPLGI.png?height=468&width=1397)\\n\\n**Cupids** connect people in Mundo Lingo (though not for love, just for friends). After reading this you will be a total master of the social landscape and you will do it well ğŸ”¥\\n\\n## The Art of Introducing People\\n\\nğŸ¦‹ Letâ€™s turn those **loners** into **social butterflies**. The easiest way to do that, will surprise you. Here it is:\\n\\n**RolePlay |** Here we have 2 people. â€œ**Loner**â€ and â€œ**Match**â€ ğŸ™â€â™‚ï¸ - - ğŸ™‹ğŸ½â€â™€ï¸\\n\\n1. ğŸ™â€â™‚ï¸ Approach **Loner**, ask their name, make light conversation.\\n2. Ask **Loner** â€œ*There are other speakers of your language in this event, can I introduce you?*â€\\n3. If **Loner** say yes, ask them to wait there *(not follow you)* while you go to talk with the **match**. The **match** should be someone, or some people who are standing and have similar flags.\\n4. ğŸ™‹ğŸ½â€â™€ï¸Ask **Match** (or **matches**) if you can introduce someone to them. If **Match** say yes, ask their name and tell them to wait there *(not follow you)*.\\n5. ğŸ™â€â™‚ï¸Return to the **Loner** and ask them to follow you. Take **Loner** to the **Match**.\\n6. ğŸ™â€â™‚ï¸ - - ğŸ™‹ğŸ½â€â™€ï¸Introduce **Match** and **Loner** by name.\\n7. Nowâ€¦.  run away! ğŸ˜± Go! Donâ€™t even say anything, just get out of there!\\n\\n### Why??\\n\\nIt may feel bad randomly running away but it works. Giving them the privacy to meet each other without the feeling of you watching is **waaay** easier. If you feel too bad, just say *â€œExcuse me, Iâ€™ll be right backâ€* and exit. You donâ€™t actually have to come back. However you do it, donâ€™t wait around while they meet each other, it only makes it more awkward.\\n\\n## Now what?\\n\\nNext up, how to be a [Vulture Hunter](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/kQBwhQlTdsO8KCXfgG3OJn_ej4pmC5ZUCfO